name: propellant-laboratory-complex-area-1-30
notes: Description: In Area 1-30 there are over 30 buildings that support solid rocket propellant research and development, formulating, mixing, casting, curing and measuring of physical properties of solid propellants. The facilities consist of shop support and motor case preparation work areas for solid motor propellant grains, test pads for rocket motors with thrusts up to 5,000 lbs, covering pads and bunkers for steady storage of propellants, and over 11 research cells, some of which are equipped with remote manipulators for processing high energy propellants. The area also contains environmental chambers used to condition and age rocket propellants, and laboratory rooms to prepare and analyze propellants and their constituents. The facilities can mix propellant from 1/4 to 50 gallons in quantity and conduct every test known for propellant hazard analysis.  Purpose: Small-scale creation and evaluation of propellants, especially solid rocket propellants. Formulate, mixing, and testing of propellants and evaluation of physical properties and other behaviors.  Products: Propellant Formulation, Propellant Mixing, Propellant Testing, Analysis of Propellant Physical Properties
title: Propellant Laboratory Complex (Area 1-30)
